FBIS3-7991 "dreeu042_h_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 HUNGARY New Hungarian Army Commander Appointed LD0103145794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1200 GMT 1 Mar 94 LD0103145794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] Lieutenant-General Janos Deak has been appointed commander of the Hungarian Army; at the same time the retiring commander Colonel-General Kalman Loerincz has been relieved of the post. For his excellent work in the maintenance of Hungary's military defense capability, in the establishment of the Hungarian Army's national image, and in the upholding of its military preparedness, the retiring army commander was presented the Hungarian Republic's Medium Cross Order of Merit decorated with a Star, by President of the Republic Arpad Goencz. [Defense Minister] Lajos Fur presented an ornamental saber to Kalman Loerincz. Arpad Goencz stressed in his speech that Hungary's security could be guaranteed by having an army which was not only able to defend the country but able even to deter a possible aggressor.
